HB 367 Original 2026 Regular Session Butler
Abstract: Revises the time period for providing notice of an adjudicatory hearing of the
Structural Pest Control Commission.
Present law authorizes the commission to impose civil penalties, probation, and suspend or
revoke permits, licenses, and registrations based on an adjudicatory hearing conducted in
accordance with the Administrative Procedure Act (APA). Further requires the commission
to provide the alleged violator with at least 30 days of notice of an adjudicatory hearing by
certified mail.
Proposed law modifies present law by requiring a hearing notice be provided in accordance
with the APA instead of requiring a minimum 30-day notice period.
(Amends R.S. 3:3372(E)(2))
